On 09-05-2012 15:46, Aaron Binns wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Nicholas Clarke &lt;nicl@... &lt;mailto:nicl%40kb.dk&gt;&gt; writes:
&gt;
&gt; &gt; However I would like to be able to get a list of the warc headers in a
&gt; &gt; record and also a copy of the complete header as a byte array.
&gt;
&gt; Hmm, I don&#39;t think you can get the warc headers as a byte array. The
&gt; code that parses the headers out of the underlying byte stream consumes
&gt; those bytes from the stream so that the file pointer is at the end of
&gt; the warc headers once they are parsed.
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;m curious, what do you want to do with the bytes of the warc headers,
&gt; if you were able to get them?
&gt;
Basically I would like to be able to read a warc header and use the 
information, which is possible, but I would also like to be able to 
stream the header and record to a new file. So I would like to read the 
header normally to validate that it is actually a &quot;valid&quot; warc header 
and then output the header and payload to some other stream. And to 
output the header I would prefer the raw bytes. I suppose I may be able 
to assemble a facsimile using |*getHeaderFields 
&lt;http://crawler.archive.org/apidocs/org/archive/io/ArchiveRecordHeader.html#getHeaderFields%28%29&gt;*()| 
and an iterator but that would be displeasing.

If anything fails I could probably use my own warc reader. But I would 
like to avoid that for now.

-Nicholas


